article.headline: Cent. Michigan 67, N. Illinois 64
article.story: DEKALB, Ill. (AP) -- Giordan Watson scored 28 points and handed out a game-high five assists Saturday to lead Central Michigan to a 67-64 win over Northern Illinois. After two free throws by Northern Illinois' Shaun Logan pulled the Huskies to within 65-64 with 52 seconds left, Watson missed a jumper, but Robbie Harman grabbed the offensive rebound for Central Michigan. Watson was then fouled with 7 seconds left, and he made both free throws. Zach Pancratz missed a 3-pointer in the closing seconds that would have sent the game into overtime. Marko Spica came off the bench to score 18 points and grab a game-high eight rebounds for the Chippewas (7-8, 2-1 Mid-American). Central Michigan outrebounded the Huskies 37-26, and the Chippewa bench outscored the Northern Illinois reserves 29-4. Logan led Northern Illinois (4-11, 1-2) with 23 points, and Mike McKinney chipped in 15 points and four rebounds.
